HttpServletRequest is a Java interface.

👉 Short meaning:
It represents the incoming HTTP request from the client (browser/Postman).

💡 In simple words:

👉 “What did the client send to the server?” → stored here

⚡ It contains:
Request data (body)
Headers (Authorization, Content-Type)
Parameters (query params)
URL info
Cookies
🧠 Example:
String token = request.getHeader("Authorization");

👉 Used to get JWT token from request

🔥 In your Spring Boot project:
Client sends request → comes as HttpServletRequest
You extract:
JWT token
user data
request params
⚡ One line:

HttpServletRequest = object that holds all data sent by client to server

