BCryptPasswordEncoder is a class in Spring Security.

👉 Short meaning:
It is used to encrypt (hash) passwords securely before saving them in the database.

💡 In simple words:

👉 “Convert plain password → secure unreadable form”


RestTemplate is a class in Spring Boot / Spring Framework used to make HTTP calls to other APIs (services) from your application.

🔹 Simple Meaning

👉 It helps your backend talk to another backend.

🔹 Why we use RestTemplate

In your microservices project (like your Auth Service → User Service → Problem Service), services need to communicate.

Instead of writing raw HTTP code, you use RestTemplate.

🔹 What it can do

RestTemplate allows you to:

Send GET request → fetch data
Send POST request → create data
Send PUT request → update data
Send DELETE request → delete data
🔹 Example (VERY IMPORTANT)
👉 Scenario:

Your Auth Service wants to call User Service

RestTemplate restTemplate = new RestTemplate();

String url = "http://localhost:8082/users/email/test@gmail.com";

User user = restTemplate.getForObject(url, User.class);
🔹 Common Methods
1. GET
restTemplate.getForObject(url, ResponseType.class);
2. POST
restTemplate.postForObject(url, requestBody, ResponseType.class);
3. PUT
restTemplate.put(url, requestBody);
4. DELETE
restTemplate.delete(url);